International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 28 Oct 2021 23:27 PDT
Source: KGW [abridged, edited]
https://www.kgw.com/article/news/local/legionnaires-disease-beaverton/283-b39aba49-ce06-4931-aae3-afb56969e5cb


Washington County [Oregon] Public Health is investigating 6 cases of Legionnaires' disease reported within the last week in the Murrayhill area of Beaverton. Four people have been hospitalized. The county said those infected range in age from late 40s to early 80s and live within 2 miles of Murray Boulevard and Scholls Ferry Road.

Health officials have not identified the source of the infection and want to warn people in the area to look out for symptoms. Washington County Public Health is working with the Oregon Health Authority and the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention to collect samples and conduct tests to determine the sources of the exposure.

Legionnaires' disease is a type of pneumonia caused by _Legionella_ bacteria found naturally in the environment. Common sources of infection include hot tubs, hot water tanks, large air conditioning and plumbing systems, and fountains. People can become infected by breathing in droplets from contaminated water, according to Washington County Public Health.

[Byline: Alma McCarty]

